Vheadline
p2
VA grand event indeed
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe Department of Culture started the concept of holding monthly music concerts  to promote and popularise the traditional music of the State. Organisations such as Bhubaneswar Music Circle and Odissi Research Centre (ORC) are part of  the project. The latest concert was hosted in association with the ORC.The concert featured songs composed by Gopalkrushna. It commenced with a chorusBhajamana brajarajankuthat was followed by a very popular numberUthilu edebegi kahnikire dukhidhanaby Lata Ghosh. Bijaya Jena and Sangeeta Gosain&#8217;s recitals were based on raga Kirwani and Bilahari respectively.Shyamaku juhara tara premaku juhara, another popular number, was rendered by Keshab Rout followed by renditions by Binapani Nayak and Chandramani Lenka.Bharati Jena and Nazia Alam regaled with their duet. And as a fitting finale, versatile vocalist and composer Ramahari Das mesmerised with the numberDhira samirefor which legendary Balakrushna Dash had scored the music.
